- Make UI so that when adding an app it opens a modal window where the user can browse for an app.
  Once the user has chosen a path take the basename and assume that as the host.
- at startup check if passenger is installed, if not run Installer.app.
- Show list of rails apps that are found in /etc/apache2/passenger_apps/*.vhost.conf
- Adding a new app:
  - Let the user browse to app root
  - Create new vhost file for app
  - Add host with: $ sudo niload hosts . < hosts.txt
  - Restart Apache
- Restarting apps, by touching tmp/restart.txt